WorkItem.Description:
JSDocs are not being correctly applied to autogenerated properties.

For example,
``` TypeScript
/**
 * Four legged animal.
 */
class Dog {
	/**
	 * Creates a Dog.
	 * @param name The name of the Dog.
	 */
	constructor(public name: string){}
}

var a = new Dog('rover');
a.name = ...
```
You'd expect when assigning to `name` or mousing over it, that Intellisense would tell give you the same description as applied via the `param` tag on the constructor. This is the only feasible way to get JSDoc Intellisense on autogened properties, so I hope this issue is tackled at some point.

[Playground reproduction](http://www.typescriptlang.org/Playground/#src=%2F**%0A%20*%20Four%20legged%20animal.%0A%20*%2F%0Aclass%20Dog%20%7B%0A%09%2F**%0A%09%20*%20Creates%20a%20Dog.%0A%09%20*%20%40param%20name%20The%20name%20of%20the%20Dog.%0A%09%20*%2F%0A%09constructor(public%20name%3A%20string)%7B%7D%0A%7D%0A%0Avar%20a%20%3D%20new%20Dog('rover')%3B%0Aa.name)

Comments.Message:
Workaround:

```
class Dog {
	/**
	 * Creates a Dog.
	 * @param name The name of the Dog.
	 */
	constructor(/** The name of the dog */public name: string){}
}
```
